Sentencas: Solution precursor plasma spraying (SPPS) was employed to prepare porous La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM) cathode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying

Sentencas: The surface morphology and microstructure of the LSM deposits were characterized by SEM.
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying

Sentencas: The phase structure of LSM was analyzed by XRD.
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying

Sentencas: The electrochemical behavior was investigated through the impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying

Sentencas: The effect of spray distance and annealing treatment on SPPS LSM microstructure was examined.
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying

Sentencas: Annealing at 1050 degrees C for 2 h in air, the coherent porous films of the perovskite phase with a fine microstructure were presented.
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying

Sentencas: The results show that the microstructure of SPPS LSM cathode exhibits a significant influence on the cathode polarization.
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying

Sentencas: The lowest specific surface resistance of 0.3 Omega-cm(2) is obtained at 1000 degrees C for SPPS LSM cathode deposited at a spray distance of 60 mm.
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying

Sentencas: SPPS is a promising process to fabricate SOFC cathode with tailoring of the desired phase and microstructure.
Titulo: Microstructure and Electrochemical Behavior of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 Deposited by Solution Precursor Plasma Spraying
